&lt;h2&gt;C++/Kotlin Software Developer (RustRover Debugger)&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You care deeply about how developer tools are built, especially when it comes to the intricacies of debugging. You enjoy solving complex, low-level problems and want to make the Rust ecosystem better for everyone.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About JetBrains&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We create intelligent software development tools for developers and teams. More than 15 million users, over 300,000 companies, and 88 of the Fortune Global Top 100 rely on our products to solve real, complex problems. Our mission is simple: make development teams more productive and AI adoptable at scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Rust is growing fast. To give the community a dedicated, smart IDE, we released RustRover, a core part of which is the debugger. Right now, it sets a high bar, but there&#39;s plenty of room to push it further – both by building new features and by untangling tricky configurations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Software Developer on the RustRover team, you’ll take ownership of the RustRover debugger&#39;s state, driving its development across two interconnected parts: the OS-specific C++ debugger (LLDB or GDB) and the IntelliJ-based Java/Kotlin client. You’ll work independently but collaborate closely with our flat, cross-functional team of developers, QA specialists, and support engineers to make debugging Rust applications smoother and more reliable.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Day to day, you will:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Improve and expand the RustRover debugger across its C++ backend and Java/Kotlin frontend.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement new IDE run/debug configurations, such as remote development support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Enhance Rust expression evaluation capabilities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Investigate and fix OS-specific SIGSEGV errors in C++ code from LLDB.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design clear, maintainable code and ensure the algorithms behind it are sound.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll bring&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A genuine interest in making development and debugging more convenient.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort taking ownership of complex problems and figuring things out.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;An appreciation for clean, readable, and maintainable code.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A proactive approach to communication and the ability to work independently.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Openness to diverse opinions and the ability to explain your reasoning clearly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A drive to master new approaches, technologies, and paradigms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What you’ll need&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong proficiency in C++ programming.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A solid understanding of system programming and multi-process communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A strong grasp of software development processes and life cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic knowledge of Java or Kotlin, or a readiness to learn quickly.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with compiler development, LLVM/LLDB, or low-level debugging on various OS platforms is a strong plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with other languages like Rust, Clojure, Python, Ruby, or Haskell is also a plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What success looks like&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success in this role means you&#39;re independently driving improvements in the RustRover debugger, bridging the gap between the C++ backend and the Kotlin/Java client. You are actively solving complex configuration issues, introducing reliable new features, and leaving the codebase cleaner than you found it. Ultimately, you are earning the trust of the Rust community by making their debugging experience significantly smoother.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why join JetBrains?&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;l

&lt;p&gt;Kineto is a next-generation platform that enables creators, educators, and small businesses to generate, deploy, and operate fully functional AI-powered web applications – instantly and at scale.&amp;nbsp;It combines LLM-driven code generation, multi-tenant Postgres (Neon), dynamic hosting (GKE and Knative), automated deployments (Flux), analytics, billing, and a seamless chat-based UX to make software creation accessible to everyone. Our team is growing rapidly, and we’re now seeking an experienced Infrastructure Engineer who can design, build, and maintain our cloud-native platform, with a focus on scalability, reliability, and automated operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;What you’ll do:&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Cloud and platform engineering (DevOps):&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, implement, and manage the core infrastructure powering Kineto&#39;s platform on Google Cloud Platform (GCP), including networking, security, and identity management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and operate resilient, highly available distributed systems using Kubernetes (GKE), Knative, Istio, and related cloud-native technologies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Automate the entire infrastructure life cycle (IaC) using Terraform and Terragrunt, ensuring secure, reproducible, and auditable environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement and maintain CI/CD pipelines (e.g. GitHub Actions and TeamCity) and deployment tools like Flux and Helm for GitOps-driven application delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Optimize and manage the multi-tenant data layer on Postgres and Neon, focusing on robust tenant isolation, performance, backups, and safe schema management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Operational excellence and reliability:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Drive site reliability engineering (SRE) practices, including monitoring, alerting (Prometheus, Grafana), logging (Loki), and incident response.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Solve complex operational challenges, such as optimizing scale to zero for cost efficiency, minimizing cold starts, enhancing autoscaling behavior, and managing queue backpressure.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Implement platform-wide performance tuning (e.g. container resource limits, distributed locks, caching strategies, and GC configurations).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure platform security and compliance by implementing best practices for secrets management, network segmentation, and vulnerability scanning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Technical leadership:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own major infrastructure roadmap items, including multi-region deployments, disaster recovery planning, advanced tenancy separation, and ephemeral preview environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Champion DevOps and SRE principles across the engineering team, mentoring engineers on cloud-native best practices, operational readiness, and debugging complex distributed systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with product and engineering teams to define the long-term vision for the platform&#39;s architecture and operational model.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;We’d be glad to have you on our team if you:&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have five or more years of experience building and operating large-scale, commercial cloud-native infrastructure, with a strong focus on DevOps/SRE practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Possess deep, hands-on expertise with GCP (or AWS/Azure) and Kubernetes administration and operations (GKE experience is a strong plus).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are proficient with infrastructure-as-code (IaC) tools, particularly Terraform, for managing complex environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have a solid understanding of Linux internals, networking (CNI and service mesh), security, and distributed system design.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are familiar with CI/CD tools, GitOps (e.g. Flux), monitoring stacks (Prometheus/Grafana), and logging systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Thrive in cross-functional teams and excel at communicating complex infrastructure ideas

&lt;p&gt;JetBrains is a leading software vendor specializing in the creation of intelligent development tools, including IDEs and team tools used by millions of professionals around the world. The company is also renowned for developing the Kotlin programming language, Google&#39;s preferred language for Android development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are now looking for a highly analytical and experienced Compensation and Benefits Specialist to join our global team. In this role, you will be the subject matter expert for our benefits portfolio, drive our global mobility initiatives, design and handle competitive recognition programs, and partner closely with the Sales organization to ensure a robust job architecture and incentive programs.&lt;/p&gt;
